main event: A circular object, changing color and moving erratically, was observed by ground and air personnel over Anchorage, Alaska on December 17, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for 16-37 minutes, ranging from 5 miles to over 30 miles out.
The object's movements were correlated with an echo from the University of Alaska, suggesting it may have been a balloon.
Previous sightings of a similar object had been reported in the area over the past 3 weeks.
The object was observed making a slight right turn before going out of sight below the horizon.
The sighting was observed by multiple Air Traffic Control specialists at the Anchorage International Airport.
sighted object: Circular object, changing color and moving erratically
